01:32.926 --> 01:36.346
<i>Stone's Rules are things
that I have learned in life</i>

01:36.429 --> 01:38.519
that I seek to pass on to others

01:38.598 --> 01:42.058
who may want to be in the
same business that I'm in.

01:42.144 --> 01:44.564
Or, actually, any business,
'cause they are fully applicable.

01:44.647 --> 01:46.437
So, for example, a Stone's Rule:

01:46.523 --> 01:50.113
"It is better to be infamous
than never be famous at all."

01:50.193 --> 01:51.403
Stone's Rule.

01:56.700 --> 02:00.620
One man's dirty trick is
another man's political, civic action.

02:00.704 --> 02:02.964
Everything I do, everything
I've done, has been legal.

02:03.581 --> 02:07.291
<i>But politics ain't beanbag
and losers don't legislate.</i>

02:07.377 --> 02:10.007
The truth will be
suppressed no longer.

02:10.088 --> 02:12.258
Lock her up!

02:12.340 --> 02:13.760
Lock her up!

02:13.842 --> 02:16.512
Well, Roger has a
really rough reputation.

02:16.594 --> 02:19.394
They talk about "dirty trickster"
and lots of other things,

02:19.472 --> 02:24.852
but I've known him for a long
time, and he's actually a quality guy.

02:24.937 --> 02:26.397
He's a nice guy.

02:26.479 --> 02:27.899
Just a few
descriptions of you here:

02:27.981 --> 02:30.481
"a state-of-the-art
sleazeball," "a little rat,"

02:30.567 --> 02:32.277
"an actor who likes
to assume poses."

02:32.360 --> 02:33.700
<i>I believe in winning.</i>

02:33.779 --> 02:37.699
<i>I believe in doing whatever is
necessary to win, short of breaking the law.</i>

02:37.783 --> 02:41.203
In the world of political consulting,
there are a number of rogues.

02:41.286 --> 02:42.286
But there's...

02:42.370 --> 02:44.710
There's really nobody
quite like Roger Stone.

02:44.790 --> 02:48.540
Roger is the sinister Forrest
Gump of American politics.

02:48.626 --> 02:54.926
<i>He's not just this simpleminded guy,
but this Machiavellian, almost crazy guy</i>

02:55.008 --> 02:58.928
<i>who shows up at every key
moment in recent American history.</i>

03:03.350 --> 03:05.020
Roger has a great
understanding of the media.

03:05.102 --> 03:08.192
He understands politics and
he understands politicians.

03:08.271 --> 03:11.111
And he always likes
to take on somebody

03:11.191 --> 03:13.401
that at least has a
good chance of winning,

03:13.485 --> 03:15.065
and sometimes it
doesn't work out.

03:15.153 --> 03:18.283
He's had some people that I said,
"What are you doing with these people?"

03:18.365 --> 03:21.155
But, you know... But he
loves it and he loves the game.

03:21.243 --> 03:23.453
He has fun with it,
and he's very good at it.

03:25.956 --> 03:30.376
<i>Roger Stone created
Donald Trump as a political figure.</i>

03:30.460 --> 03:35.920
There is no doubt that in
tone, in affect, in profile,

03:36.008 --> 03:40.848
the Trump candidacy was a
pure Roger Stone production.

03:40.929 --> 03:43.349
When Mexico sends its people...

03:43.432 --> 03:45.062
They're bringing drugs,

03:45.142 --> 03:47.772
they're bringing crime,
they're rapists.

03:47.853 --> 03:50.313
And some, I assume,
are good people.

03:50.397 --> 03:53.357
<i>Whereas the
rest of us looked at Trump</i>

03:53.441 --> 03:56.691
<i>and saw someone who was
impossibly vulgar and impolite,</i>

03:56.779 --> 04:00.529
Roger looked at him and said, "You know,
this is someone who voters might like."

04:00.615 --> 04:03.075
I mean, Roger actually
gets democracy in a way,

04:03.160 --> 04:05.830
I think most people
who cover politics don't.

04:05.913 --> 04:09.293
You know, democracy is the
process of appealing to the majority.

04:12.669 --> 04:13.919
My name's Donald Trump,

04:14.004 --> 04:16.303
and I'm the largest real
estate developer in New York.

04:16.380 --> 04:21.851
<i>I own buildings all over the place,
model agencies, the Miss Universe pageant.</i>

04:21.928 --> 04:23.349
But it wasn't always so easy.

04:23.430 --> 04:26.930
About 13 years ago,
I was billions of dollars in debt.

04:27.517 --> 04:30.897
<i>But I fought back
and I won, big league.</i>

04:30.979 --> 04:35.359
<i>Now my company is bigger than it ever
