58:26.586 --> 58:29.666
There is such a thing.
- Of course, but I see none here.

58:29.756 --> 58:30.916
Okay, as far as
you're concerned.

58:31.008 --> 58:33.008
The whole "birther" movement,

58:33.093 --> 58:38.433
which was so crazy and
so wrong and so racist,

58:38.515 --> 58:42.805
that is the basis of
Trump's political appeal.

58:50.610 --> 58:52.530
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

58:53.113 --> 58:55.203
I am officially running...

58:57.534 --> 59:00.414
...for president of
the United States,

59:00.495 --> 59:05.165
<i>and we are going to make
our country great again.</i>

59:05.250 --> 59:07.250
What's your precise
role with Donald Trump?

59:07.335 --> 59:08.995
Are you a paid advisor?
- Uh... I am now.

59:09.088 --> 59:13.588
I'm just helping as a general
communications strategist, I guess.

59:13.675 --> 59:16.465
People get the impression that this
is performance art for Donald Trump.

59:16.553 --> 59:19.513
Is he serious about being
president of the United States?

59:19.598 --> 59:24.098
I will build a great, great
wall on our southern border,

59:24.186 --> 59:27.016
and I will have Mexico
pay for that wall.

59:27.106 --> 59:28.106
Yes!
- Mark my words.

59:28.190 --> 59:29.360
Is this a president talking?

59:29.441 --> 59:30.691
If there is one murder,

59:30.775 --> 59:34.605
if there is one crime by someone who
is not supposed to be in the country,

59:34.696 --> 59:35.986
that's one crime too many.

59:36.073 --> 59:40.583
I think Trump has identified a
legitimate hot-button issue.

59:40.660 --> 59:44.830
"Donald J. Trump is calling for
a total and complete shutdown

59:44.914 --> 59:47.884
of Muslims entering
the United States

59:47.959 --> 59:54.879
until our country's representatives can
figure out what the hell is going on."

59:56.676 --> 59:58.676
<i>Roger Stone came
to power with Nixon.</i>

59:58.762 --> 01:00:01.142
And Nixon, of course, had
the Southern strategy,

01:00:01.223 --> 01:00:04.853
<i>which was all about milking
people's racial resentments,</i>

01:00:04.934 --> 01:00:07.564
<i>and in the case of Trump,
anti-immigrant resentments.</i>

01:00:08.146 --> 01:00:11.226
Working up hate that would turn
them against the government

01:00:11.316 --> 01:00:14.186
and against the so-called
elites who were in government.

01:00:14.278 --> 01:00:17.198
The political system
is a cesspool.

01:00:17.281 --> 01:00:18.241
<i>I've been a lobbyist.</i>

01:00:18.323 --> 01:00:21.033
<i>I worked on the Senate side.
I worked on the House side.</i>

01:00:21.118 --> 01:00:22.658
<i>I saw how the sausage are made.</i>

01:00:22.744 --> 01:00:24.834
<i>The whole process
is deeply corrupt.</i>

01:00:25.705 --> 01:00:27.615
<i>Trump is the only one
who can clean it up.</i>

01:00:27.707 --> 01:00:29.537
<i>Trump!
Trump! Trump!</i>

01:00:29.626 --> 01:00:33.166
Trump! Trump! Trump!

01:00:33.255 --> 01:00:37.585
We are going to Washington, DC,

01:00:37.676 --> 01:00:40.926
and we are going to do what?

01:00:41.012 --> 01:00:43.722
Drain the swamp.

01:00:45.267 --> 01:00:46.767
It is so corrupt.

01:00:46.851 --> 01:00:50.651
The best part is that he's just kicking
the political establishment in the balls.

01:00:50.730 --> 01:00:54.980
They are shitting a brick, because
he's challenging the status quo.

01:00:55.068 --> 01:00:57.698
All these other candidates are
really for the status quo.

01:00:57.779 --> 01:01:03.159
Roger's the ultimate insider, which
makes him incredibly good at seeing

01:01:03.243 --> 01:01:06.543
how to package someone he
could sell as an outsider.

01:01:06.621 --> 01:01:10.121
We are going to stand up
for the American worker

01:01:10.209 --> 01:01:14.589
like nobody has ever stood
up for that worker before.

01:01:15.464 --> 01:01:19.054
There is real upset over
jobs, over globalization,

01:01:19.133 --> 01:01:23.643
<i>over people losing their sort
of status and their incomes.</i>

01:01:23.722 --> 01:01:26.772
You know, there are all kinds
of answers to these questions,

01:01:26.850 --> 01:01:29.770
but the answers that he's
provided, for the most part,

01:01:29.853 --> 01:01:32.563
are the answers that
billionaires are interested in.

01:01:32.647 --> 01:01:37.937
We're also going to eliminate
job-killing regulations.

01:01:38.862 --> 01:01:43.782
And lift the restrictions on the
production of American energy,

01:01:43.867 --> 01:01:50.287
including shale, oil, natural
gas and beautiful, clean coal.

01:01:50.374 --> 01:01:53.214
There's no grassroots movement

01:01:53.293 --> 01:01:57.513
to gut the EPA and give people
dirty water and dirty air.

01:01:57.589 --> 01:02:01.929
The only people who are really caring
about that are the polluting industries.

01:02:02.010 --> 01:02:04.890
They say I have the most loyal people.
Did you ever see that?

01:02:04.971 --> 01:02:06.771
Where I could stand in the
middle of Fifth Avenue

01:02:06.848 --> 01:02:09.598
and shoot somebody, and I
wouldn't lose any voters, okay?

01:02:09.684 --> 01:02:11.354
It's, like, incredible.

01:02:11.436 --> 01:02:14.606
Roger understands that I've
always gotten great ratings,

01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:18.359
whether it's on <i>The Apprentice</i>
or virtually any interview,

01:02:18.443 --> 01:02:19.993
and that's why people
want to interview me.

01:02:20.069 --> 01:02:23.029
And I think that's one of the things
that's always fascinated Roger,

01:02:23.114 --> 01:02:26.414
because, ultimately, it
is all about the ratings

01:02:26.493 --> 01:02:29.083
and it is all about people
watching and the eyeballs.

01:02:29.162 --> 01:02:33.212
Mr. Trump, you've called women
you don't like "fat pigs,"

01:02:33.292 --> 01:02:37.502
"dogs," "slobs," and
"disgusting animals."

01:02:37.587 --> 01:02:40.207
Your Twitter account...
- Only Rosie O'Donnell.

01:02:41.508 --> 01:02:44.298
Unlike every other candidate
I have ever worked with,

01:02:44.386 --> 01:02:48.136
he is unscripted, he is
unrehearsed, he is unhandled.

01:02:48.222 --> 01:02:51.732
Contrast that with Jeb Bush, who
looks both bored and annoyed,

01:02:51.810 --> 01:02:56.150
like, "Just... This is mine. Just
anoint me and give it to me.

01:02:56.230 --> 01:02:59.070
Father, Father, tell them
it's my turn to be king."

01:02:59.150 --> 01:03:00.610
Roger,
before you go,

01:03:00.694 --> 01:03:03.784
uh, will you remain with the Donald
now throughout the campaign?

01:03:03.863 --> 01:03:06.163
I'll do whatever the
Donald asks me to do.

01:03:07.492 --> 01:03:08.992
<i>Good evening.
It's been 48 hours</i>

01:03:09.077 --> 01:03:11.157
since the first Republican
presidential debate,

01:03:11.245 --> 01:03:14.785
and a testy exchange between Donald
Trump and moderator Megyn Kelly

01:03:14.874 --> 01:03:16.634
has become a flash
point in the campaign.

01:03:16.710 --> 01:03:20.000
<i>You know, you could see there
was blood coming out of her eyes, uh,</i>

01:03:20.088 --> 01:03:22.668
<i>blood coming out
of her wherever.</i>

01:03:22.757 --> 01:03:26.177
Now members of the Republican field
are lining up to criticize him.

01:03:26.260 --> 01:03:29.680
And word this evening that an advisor
and a longtime friend of Trump's

01:03:29.764 --> 01:03:31.484
has resigned from the campaign.

01:03:31.558 --> 01:03:33.388
Trump says he fired him.

01:03:33.477 --> 01:03:34.807
<i>Roger
Stone's a nice guy,</i>

01:03:34.894 --> 01:03:37.774
<i>but I let him go because I
really wasn't using him,</i>

01:03:37.856 --> 01:03:41.736
<i>and he liked to get a lot of publicity
for himself, which I didn't want.</i>

01:03:41.818 --> 01:03:44.068
He's real, he's genuine,
and it's entertaining.

01:03:44.153 --> 01:03:45.663
That's why he's doing so well.

01:03:46.323 --> 01:03:49.783
So why'd he fire you?
- He didn't. I quit.

01:03:49.868 --> 01:03:52.198
"Oh, you can't fire me.
I quit!"

01:03:53.997 --> 01:03:56.957
<i>Did he get fired or
did he quit? I don't know.</i>

01:03:57.041 --> 01:03:59.001
He still hasn't admitted
to me that he got fired,

01:03:59.085 --> 01:04:00.955
and I've tried numerous times.

01:04:01.045 --> 01:04:02.545
"Bullshit, you got fired.
Come on."

01:04:02.631 --> 01:04:03.631
"No, no, no!"

01:04:03.715 --> 01:04:06.585
Because Roger, you know, Roger the
feminist, was really offended

01:04:06.676 --> 01:04:09.296
about what Trump said
about Megyn Kelly.

01:04:10.179 --> 01:04:11.929
<i>I don't need
the Trump campaign</i>

01:04:12.015 --> 01:04:14.055
<i>to generate press
coverage for myself,</i>

01:04:14.142 --> 01:04:17.062
<i>and I can get in the
tabloids any time I want.</i>

01:04:17.145 --> 01:04:19.855
But to say that you want me
to work on your campaign,

01:04:19.939 --> 01:04:21.939
but you don't want me
to talk to reporters

01:04:22.025 --> 01:04:23.775
would be like saying to me,

01:04:23.860 --> 01:04:26.570
"I just don't want you to breathe
air between now and November.

01:04:26.655 --> 01:04:28.945
If you could just agree
not to breathe any air

01:04:29.032 --> 01:04:31.242
or eat any food,
everything will be fine."

01:04:31.325 --> 01:04:35.115
Talking to reporters is what I do.
That's my value.

01:04:35.204 --> 01:04:37.874
Roger Stone and I don't agree on anything.
I don't...

01:04:37.957 --> 01:04:40.747
He does not represent the
Trump campaign. - Not what he says.

01:04:40.835 --> 01:04:42.665
What Roger Stone says
and what the truth are

01:04:42.754 --> 01:04:44.554
are two factually very
different things.

01:04:44.631 --> 01:04:47.551
<i>There's no question
Lewandowski worked behind the scenes</i>

01:04:47.634 --> 01:04:49.554
<i>to get Roger thrown
out of the campaign.</i>

01:04:49.636 --> 01:04:52.006
He is an expert at stabbing
people in the back.

01:04:52.096 --> 01:04:55.266
That guy's got an incredible
capacity for treachery.

01:04:55.349 --> 01:04:58.559
By the way, I spoke to a Polish
language expert the other day.

01:04:58.645 --> 01:05:02.855
I was unaware of the fact that
Lewandowski, loosely translated,

01:05:02.941 --> 01:05:04.321
means "cocksucker."

01:05:04.984 --> 01:05:09.744
Well, Roger is a tough guy, and
Roger will make enemies sometimes

01:05:09.823 --> 01:05:12.413
that I always say, there's
no reason for it.

01:05:13.034 --> 01:05:14.204
<i>Roger is older now,</i>

01:05:14.285 --> 01:05:18.995
<i>and I think he sees
the Trump campaign,</i>

01:05:19.082 --> 01:05:22.422
at once as his creation,

01:05:22.502 --> 01:05:28.682
but also something that he's not
allowed to participate in day to day.

01:05:28.758 --> 01:05:32.508
And that, understandably,
makes him sad.

01:05:32.596 --> 01:05:34.386
<i>I have no
interest in going back.</i>

01:05:34.473 --> 01:05:37.893
<i>Although I strongly support Trump,
we have managerial differences.</i>

01:05:37.976 --> 01:05:41.556
And, meanwhile, I'm just making the very
best case for him in public that I can,

01:05:41.646 --> 01:05:44.396
'cause I do think he
has what it takes.

01:05:44.483 --> 01:05:48.193
There's always this tension between
the candidate and his consultant.

01:05:48.277 --> 01:05:52.157
The candidate resents the credit
the consultant gets for his words.

01:05:52.240 --> 01:05:55.790
<i>The consultant resents, you know, the
fame and fortune the candidate gets</i>

01:05:55.869 --> 01:05:57.329
<i>when he did all the work.</i>

01:05:57.411 --> 01:06:00.461
<i>And Trump hated the fact that Stone
was showing up on cable news</i>

01:06:00.540 --> 01:06:03.130
<i>and that people were, you know,
calling him Trump's brain.</i>

01:06:03.209 --> 01:06:04.209
<i>So he fired him.</i>

01:06:04.293 --> 01:06:06.253
But it doesn't mean he
stopped relying on him.

01:06:06.337 --> 01:06:08.467
It seems to me there is more
than meets the eye here

01:06:08.548 --> 01:06:11.088
with Roger Stone parting company
from the Trump campaign,

01:06:11.175 --> 01:06:14.635
coming on my program and others
and giving the big Trump pitch.

01:06:14.721 --> 01:06:17.311
You media types
are so conspiratorial.

01:06:17.390 --> 01:06:20.730
No. No, the Stone-Trump types, I
think, are the conspiratorial.

01:06:20.810 --> 01:06:21.940
Unlike...

01:06:24.523 --> 01:06:29.073
Only two campaigns have a
plausible path to the nomination.

01:06:29.152 --> 01:06:31.362
Ours and Donald Trump's.

01:06:32.071 --> 01:06:36.791
Nobody else has any mathematical
possibility, whatsoever.

01:06:36.868 --> 01:06:41.288
L-Y-I-N-apostrophe, lyin' Ted!

01:06:41.372 --> 01:06:45.292
The Bible held high, he puts
it down and then he lies.

01:06:45.376 --> 01:06:49.376
Most of the time, I win
the evangelical vote.

01:06:49.463 --> 01:06:53.763
The evangelicals, the
Christians, like Donald Trump.

01:06:53.843 --> 01:06:55.263
I'm a straight shooter.

01:06:55.344 --> 01:06:58.524
<i>After a crushing
13-point defeat in Wisconsin,</i>

01:06:58.598 --> 01:06:59.808
<i>Trump turned a page,</i>

01:06:59.891 --> 01:07:02.731
<i>sidelining campaign manager
Corey Lewandowski.</i>

01:07:02.811 --> 01:07:05.151
<i>He wasn't as effective
for the last couple of months.</i>

01:07:05.229 --> 01:07:07.769
<i>News breaking that the
GOP front-runner, by the way,</i>

01:07:07.857 --> 01:07:12.197
<i>has hired Paul Manafort to lead his
campaign's convention efforts.</i>

01:07:12.278 --> 01:07:16.698
Paul Manafort, former partner of
mine, the single best vote counter

01:07:16.783 --> 01:07:19.953
and convention strategist
in the Republican Party.

01:07:20.036 --> 01:07:23.326
When Paul Manafort got publicly
named, I got a phone call that day.

01:07:23.414 --> 01:07:25.424
And it was Roger on the
other end of the line.

01:07:25.499 --> 01:07:28.879
And you know what he sang?
"Back in the Saddle Again."

01:07:28.962 --> 01:07:30.842
I mean, Roger knows
what Roger's doing.

01:07:31.590 --> 01:07:33.470
<i>Trump asked
me to get involved</i>

01:07:33.550 --> 01:07:36.430
<i>because my reputation, among
other things in politics,</i>

01:07:36.510 --> 01:07:39.850
is understanding of the convention
process, the delegate process.

01:07:39.931 --> 01:07:42.731
And most of the major
successful big conventions

01:07:42.809 --> 01:07:45.809
over the last 30 years, I've
been intimately involved in.

01:07:45.895 --> 01:07:47.765
Did Roger recommend
you for the job?

01:07:47.856 --> 01:07:51.026
Roger was one of the two or three people
who strongly recommended me, yes.

01:07:51.109 --> 01:07:55.609
Even after Roger stopped being the
principal political advisor to Trump,

01:07:55.697 --> 01:07:57.657
he continued to be a
very important advisor,

01:07:57.740 --> 01:07:58.660
and is to this day.

01:08:02.411 --> 01:08:03.791
<i>I want to start with Roger Stone,</i>

01:08:03.872 --> 01:08:07.252
<i>because you just launched
a pro-Trump super PAC.</i>

01:08:07.333 --> 01:08:09.753
I thought, A, Donald Trump
didn't like super PACs,

01:08:09.836 --> 01:08:12.046
B, I thought you quit
or he fired you.

01:08:12.130 --> 01:08:15.720
I'm not still sure what happened there. So
what the heck is this all about, Roger?

01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:19.550
Roger told me when I was
very young, "Caputo," he says,

01:08:19.638 --> 01:08:21.178
"The media is two things.

01:08:21.264 --> 01:08:24.814
They're either evil or
they're lazy, or they're both.

01:08:24.893 --> 01:08:27.693
And if you understand that,
you can do whatever you want."

01:08:33.151 --> 01:08:37.281
Yeah, I live a pretty
Machiavellian life, and I'm a skeptic.

01:08:37.363 --> 01:08:41.703
I tend to believe the worst of people
because I understand human nature.

01:08:41.785 --> 01:08:44.245
Human nature has never changed.

01:08:44.328 --> 01:08:46.497
That's why one of Stone's
Rules is that hate

01:08:46.580 --> 01:08:48.710
is a stronger
motivator than love.

01:08:48.792 --> 01:08:50.332
That's because it is.

01:08:50.417 --> 01:08:52.917
<i>The</i> National
Enquirer <i>published a story.</i>

01:08:53.004 --> 01:08:57.634
It is a story that quoted one
source on the record, Roger Stone.

01:08:57.716 --> 01:09:01.136
<i>Let me be clear. This</i> National
Enquirer <i>story is garbage.</i>

01:09:01.220 --> 01:09:04.770
And it is a smear that has come
from Donald Trump and his henchmen.

01:09:04.849 --> 01:09:08.939
<i>One of the keys to defeating an
opponent is getting inside their head.</i>

01:09:09.020 --> 01:09:12.569
He incorrectly claims that I
am the source of this story

01:09:12.649 --> 01:09:16.488
regarding allegations that
he has been adulterous.

01:09:16.569 --> 01:09:18.819
<i>And I would note that Mr.
Stone is a man</i>

01:09:18.904 --> 01:09:21.694
who has 50 years of dirty
tricks behind him.

01:09:21.783 --> 01:09:25.703
He's a man for whom a
term was coined...

01:09:27.246 --> 01:09:28.786
for copulating with a rodent.

01:09:28.872 --> 01:09:32.002
I, of course, am quoted in
this story, on the record,

01:09:32.085 --> 01:09:36.205
saying that it would hurt him badly
with his evangelical followers.

01:09:36.296 --> 01:09:40.886
He has, as you know,
attacked me on CNN...

01:09:40.969 --> 01:09:44.389
Roger Stone has been Donald
Trump's chief political advisor.

01:09:44.471 --> 01:09:47.392
He planned and ran his
presidential campaign.

01:09:47.475 --> 01:09:49.595
...attacked me on Megyn Kelly.

01:09:49.685 --> 01:09:54.976
His entire business has been dirty tricks,
has been lies, has been personal smears.

01:09:55.066 --> 01:09:58.896
These attacks on me by him
and by his surrogates,

01:09:58.987 --> 01:10:00.857
I find this most satisfying.

01:10:00.947 --> 01:10:05.447
I hope he's laying awake at night,
worrying about what I'm going to do next.

01:10:06.035 --> 01:10:08.245
<i>He's a little bit
like the Joker in</i> Batman.

01:10:08.329 --> 01:10:10.659
<i>I mean, he gets a kick
out of doing this.</i>

01:10:10.749 --> 01:10:16.209
To some extent, his pleasure
at burning down the house

01:10:16.295 --> 01:10:18.255
is infectious for people.

01:10:18.339 --> 01:10:21.799
<i>And as a reporter, you call him up
because you want the outrageous quote.</i>

01:10:21.885 --> 01:10:24.545
You want, you know... You want
to hear what he's gonna say.

01:10:24.637 --> 01:10:27.177
He's also very plugged-in.
He's in the know.

01:10:27.265 --> 01:10:28.725
He talks to a million people.

01:10:29.308 --> 01:10:32.308
<i>I just got a call from this
reporter who was calling to warn me</i>

01:10:32.395 --> 01:10:35.685
<i>that Corey is now openly telling
people he's got the goods on Manafort.</i>

01:10:35.774 --> 01:10:39.694
He is telling reporters that
he has something on Manafort

01:10:39.778 --> 01:10:42.738
that will blow him
out of the campaign.

01:10:42.822 --> 01:10:44.822
Yeah, we gotta take
the little prick out.

01:10:46.200 --> 01:10:50.290
<i>I've been backgrounding reporters on
what a total fucking disaster he's been.</i>

01:10:50.371 --> 01:10:55.461
<i>And there's a story that just
went up by Mike Isikoff at Yahoo</i>

01:10:55.543 --> 01:10:59.883
<i>that dips into the whole
Pakistani blah, blah, blah.</i>

01:10:59.964 --> 01:11:04.144
If you look at Manafort's
long history of lobbying,

01:11:04.218 --> 01:11:07.808
it is about as controversial
as you can get.

01:11:08.597 --> 01:11:12.187
You are as connected
to the insider game

01:11:12.268 --> 01:11:14.648
of, what you've even
said on record yourself,

01:11:14.728 --> 01:11:17.068
"influence peddling,"
as anybody.

01:11:17.148 --> 01:11:19.688
How can you be the antidote
or anything to help Trump

01:11:19.776 --> 01:11:21.526
when you seem to go
against his main message?

01:11:21.610 --> 01:11:22.650
It depends on who you talk to

01:11:22.736 --> 01:11:25.276
if I'm part of the establishment
or part of the antiestablishment.

01:11:25.364 --> 01:11:27.124
You better get rid
of the super PACs

01:11:27.200 --> 01:11:30.620
because they're causing a big
problem with this country.

01:11:30.703 --> 01:11:33.333
...and a lot of bad decisions
that are being made

01:11:33.414 --> 01:11:36.134
